epgy physics p110 overview courses ohs summer schools apply and register home software research news contact epgy login course catalog physics university level p110 lessons exercises homework exams textbook p110 intermediate mechanics i scalars vectors matrices and tensors vector calculus newtonian mechanics newton's law of gravitation oscillations green's functions rotation static equilibrium of a rigid body hamilton's principle and the calculus of variations langrangian mechanics central force motion orbits motion in noninertial reference frames the epgy intermediate mechanics course covers much of what is generally covered in an upper division university mechanics course the course is a sophisticated treatment of the mechanics of particles and systems the course is designed to take 16 weeks to complete on average 4 units prequisite p070 modern physics or equivalent corequisite m53a differential equations or equivalent
